      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REWATCH (5) broke when well in the betting last week so did well to finish as close as he did, beaten less than 7m. Had strong country form prior including an easy Wagga win two back. Draws lower than last week and has winning claims with better manners. CYNICAL (9) is a progressive gelding who went to the paddock off four straight wins at this venue, the last of them in November. Tries this distance for the first time and cops a wide draw for his return but was only beaten narrowly in a recent trial. COLOSSAL HOPE (10) is going well, leading to win two back before coming from this barrier to miss by just 1.7m when third here last week. Can make an impact again. MIKI BE GOOD (7) comes off a solid fifth in the Regional Championship State final and is a two-time winner at this distance. MR TEDDY NZ (3) won two back at Newcastle then drew wider and raced parked but boxed on in this grade here last start, beaten less than 3m. Draws to be competitive.",
